#* {{quote-book|en|year=1962|chapter=9|author=Ian Fleming|title={{w|The Spy Who Loved Me (novel)|The Spy Who Loved Me}}|passage=Sluggsy said indifferently, ‘You’ll be wised up come morning. Meanwhiles, howsabout shuttin’ that dumb little hashtrap of yours? All this '''yak''' is bending my ear. I want some action.}}
